You are taking a TIER 1 EXPERT evaluation — data structures and advanced design patterns.

Solve 5 JavaScript exercises. Return your answers in Markdown using headers for the exercise IDs and code blocks for the JavaScript functions.

[1-A] Function creerFilePriorite() — a min-heap priority queue with: enqueue(val, priorite), dequeue() returns item with lowest priority number, taille() returns count.

[1-B] Function creerEventEmitter() — an EventEmitter with: on(event, fn), off(event, fn), emit(event, ...args). Supports multiple listeners per event.

[1-C] Function zip(...tableaux) — like Python zip: takes multiple arrays and returns an array of tuples.
Example: zip([1,2,3],['a','b','c']) must return [[1,'a'],[2,'b'],[3,'c']]. Stops at shortest array.

[1-D] Debugging — fix "parcoursEnLargeur" (BFS) that is broken:
function parcoursEnLargeur(graphe, depart) {
  const visites = [];
  const file = [depart];
  while (file.length > 0) {
    const noeud = file.pop();
    if (!visites.includes(noeud)) {
      visites.push(noeud);
      for (const voisin of (graphe[noeud] || [])) {
        file.push(voisin);
      }
    }
  }
  return visites;
}
Bug: uses pop() (LIFO = DFS) instead of shift() (FIFO = BFS).

[1-E] Function creerProxy(cible, gestionnaire) — an Observable proxy that intercepts get/set via a handler with: get(cible, prop) and set(cible, prop, valeur). Similar to JavaScript Proxy but implemented manually without using the Proxy built-in.

